# Minimal Dry::Types RBS stub for the rigor-dry-types demo.
#
# `Dry.Types()` returns a Module the project mixes into its own
# `Types` namespace. The plugin's scanner doesn't need to follow
# the constant resolution — it only needs to find the
# `include Dry.Types()` call. The RBS stub here is enough for
# Rigor's parser / dispatcher to accept the source without
# emitting `call.undefined-method` diagnostics on `Dry.Types`.
#
# A real project depending on `dry-types` would replace this
# with the upstream gem's own RBS (or a vendored sig discovered
# by rigor's Bundler-awareness path).

module Dry
  def self.Types: () -> Module
end
